00:22:17,440 --> 00:22:24,960
 And so, now they're being found faithful, and they rejoice that they get to share in the work of

194
00:22:24,960 --> 00:22:32,160
 Jesus, and that they even get to suffer. Now, I think there's a suffer for Jesus, not just suffer.

195
00:22:32,160 --> 00:22:36,320
 We don't rejoice in suffering. So, I have a statement here as well. "There is no joy in

196
00:22:36,320 --> 00:22:43,440
 being beaten, rejected, or treated unfairly, but there is rejoicing in suffering for being faithful

197
00:22:43,440 --> 00:22:55,280
 for Jesus." You know, big difference. And when we suffer in this way, there's also like a deeper way

198
00:22:55,280 --> 00:23:05,920
 that we commune with Jesus, because we understand his suffering in a greater way. And I've met,

199
00:23:05,920 --> 00:23:11,200
 you know, people that are persecuted Christians and in different settings, and there's just

200
00:23:11,200 --> 00:23:18,480
 something special about them. You know, they know God in a deeper way than I know God and I know

201
00:23:18,480 --> 00:23:31,760
 Jesus. And there's a deeper joy than I know, because they've communed with Jesus, you know,

202
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:38,880
 in a deeper way. And they just know for certain, and they know how Jesus has met them in these

203
00:23:38,880 --> 00:23:47,840
 difficulties. You know, I'm reminded, I was in Albania on a missions trip in the mountains.

204
00:23:47,840 --> 00:23:55,440
 It was teenage girls. There were a few Christians. Most of them were women and young teenage girls.

205
00:23:55,440 --> 00:24:00,640
 And so, I had prepared as a youth pastor. I'm just challenging message for them,

206
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:04,880
 you know, to challenge them in their faith. But then as I got to know their story, thank God,

207
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:12,560
 before I preached, I learned that there was still arranged marriages. And so, this was not a

208
00:24:12,560 --> 00:24:17,280
 Christian context. So, they were married into another religion. And then the experience was

209
00:24:17,280 --> 00:24:20,880
 that their Bibles were taken away and they were not allowed to go to church anymore.

210
00:24:22,560 --> 00:24:31,440
 You know, but to meet these young women and to see their courage and their faith and nonetheless,

211
00:24:31,440 --> 00:24:35,440
 to choose to follow Jesus, despite this being their future, they had no say in this.

212
00:24:35,440 --> 00:24:38,960
 You know, like what challenging message

213
00:24:38,960 --> 00:24:46,480
 was I going to preach to them? It was like they were challenging me with their life,

214
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:55,760
 with their faithfulness. You know, they put me trying to live a comfortable life to shame.

215
00:24:55,760 --> 00:24:59,680
 And it's not about shaming. So, I don't want to do that. But it was challenging

216
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:11,200
 and also touching and moving. So, the first reason, you know, why we can rejoice and be glad is

217
00:25:12,000 --> 00:25:17,440
 when we follow Jesus faithfully and we're persecuted, is because we are being found faithful.

218
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:27,360
 I'm going to give a second reason really quick. The second one is

219
00:25:27,360 --> 00:25:35,760
 that because we know Jesus, we can look at our present circumstances in a different light.

220
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:43,760
 Because if you're a Christian, you're a kingdom citizen. That means that you're a child of God.

221
00:25:43,760 --> 00:25:51,200
 Your future is secure. Your inheritance is secure. You can live in light of that future,

222
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:56,000
 in light of that inheritance. So, even if you experience suffering at the moment,

223
00:25:56,000 --> 00:26:03,600
 you know, you know what your future holds. And that's faith, that's supernatural. You know,

224
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:09,120
 you're not going to conjure up this courage. It's because it's given to you by the Holy Spirit.

225
00:26:09,120 --> 00:26:14,800
 It's because you're meditating on Jesus and his words and his promises. Excuse me, I'm going to

226
00:26:14,800 --> 00:26:25,920
 turn. And then that allows you, you know, to have this hope in the future that is greater

227
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:31,200
 than your present circumstances and whatever suffering your present circumstances may hold.

228
00:26:32,640 --> 00:26:41,520
 And Jesus says that your reward is great in heaven. Theirs is the kingdom. And so,

229
00:26:41,520 --> 00:26:45,520
 that allows you to have that different perspective. But I want to bring it back to us here,

230
00:26:45,520 --> 00:26:52,320
 to Hong Kong. What about us? You know, what does it mean to follow Jesus faithfully here

231
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:58,800
 in a context where there is right now no ongoing active persecution like there is in other places

232
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:04,880
 around the world? I think it's easy to dismiss these words of Jesus as applying to us.

233
00:27:04,880 --> 00:27:10,080
 Because when we think of persecution, the only thing we think of is

234
00:27:10,080 --> 00:27:18,400
 people being martyred for their faith, people being tortured, people being imprisoned.

235
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:27,440
 And I don't think I can preach a sermon without talking about the persecuted church.

236
00:27:29,760 --> 00:27:35,600
 Out of five Christians in Asia, two of them are experiencing active persecution.

237
00:27:35,600 --> 00:27:43,760
 I'll go, where is there? Five people sitting in a row there. One, two, three, four, five,

238
00:27:43,760 --> 00:27:52,240
 two people persecution for every Christian. Active persecution here in Asia. Open Doors

239
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:55,920
 has some statistics I'm going to share with you. It's an NGO that works with the persecuted church

240
00:27:55,920 --> 00:28:02,800
 and keeps statistics and records. 4,849 Christians were martyred for their faith.

241
00:28:02,800 --> 00:28:09,280
 388 million Christians around the world suffer high levels of persecution, discrimination because

242
00:28:09,280 --> 00:28:13,760
 of their faith. And over 200,000 Christians were forced to leave their home, go in hiding,

243
00:28:13,760 --> 00:28:16,720
 in country or leave their country because of their faith.

244
00:28:16,720 --> 00:28:22,960
 And these are our brothers and sisters. They are part of the body of Christ.

245
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:29,920
 And so when one part suffers or mourn, the whole body mourns. And so at the end of the service,

246
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:33,840
 we're actually going to take some time and pray for them. So I felt like I couldn't talk about

247
00:28:33,840 --> 00:28:40,640
 persecution and not talk about the circumstance and the reality of many people. But I do want

248
00:28:40,640 --> 00:28:47,600
 to bring it now back to the Hong Kong context. Just because we don't experience persecution in

249
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:54,320
 extreme measures, you know, doesn't mean that we don't experience persecution. Now, while most

250
00:28:54,320 --> 00:29:00,720
 persecution is less dramatic, it's nonetheless impactful on our lives. And I want to give you

251
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:07,360
 some examples. So maybe you're overlooked in your business, you know, where you work, where you're

252
00:29:07,360 --> 00:29:12,560
 faithfully following Jesus, you're not manipulating numbers, maybe you're not participating in the

253
00:29:12,560 --> 00:29:19,440
 office gossip. And so you're kind of an outsider. You're not liked because of that. And

254
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:26,080
 you get overlooked for all the promotions, even though you might be the most qualified person

255
00:29:26,080 --> 00:29:33,200
 that should get it. You know, so there's big impact. Maybe you're ignored when it comes to

256
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:38,320
 receiving rewards. You're a student, you're a university student, and you're open about your

257
00:29:38,320 --> 00:29:42,800
 faith, and there's somebody, a decision maker, that just doesn't like that you're a Christian,

258
00:29:42,800 --> 00:29:47,120
 because you identify with Jesus, and you're not going to get that reward,

259
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:50,800
 you're not going to get that certificate, you're not going to get that plaque, just because of that.

260
00:29:50,800 --> 00:29:58,320
 Maybe your family rejects you, you try to share the gospel with them, and

261
00:29:58,320 --> 00:30:05,040
 they didn't like that. And so they cut you off. A lot of times when people become new Christians,

262
00:30:05,600 --> 00:30:13,440
 long-term friends, over a period of time, they lose them because they now see you as a religious

263
00:30:13,440 --> 00:30:20,400
 type. So there's a cost. There's some friction, there's some tension to following Jesus. Then,

264
00:30:20,400 --> 00:30:26,080
 as I shared earlier, spiritual attacks, where the enemy pushes against us, wants to discourage us,

265
00:30:26,080 --> 00:30:33,600
 wants to keep us from trusting Jesus, following Jesus. So persecution is real, even if it's

266
00:30:33,600 --> 00:30:41,120
 less dramatic, it has an impact on our lives nonetheless. So you can see we too can experience

267
00:30:41,120 --> 00:30:47,680
 persecution. But I want to ask you a question. If you never experience any friction and tension

268
00:30:47,680 --> 00:30:53,360
 because of your faith, could it be that you have chosen comfort over faithfulness to Jesus?

269
00:31:00,240 --> 00:31:07,520
 Now, I'm not saying that we constantly need to live in this persecution and suffering and

270
00:31:07,520 --> 00:31:14,400
 these things. I don't think that's most of the time how persecution works. A lot of times it's

271
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:25,040
 more occasional or ebbs and flows. But I do think it's worth asking if there never is any friction

272
00:31:26,000 --> 00:31:38,160
 or tension because of our faith. You know, why is that? Is it because we've created this

273
00:31:38,160 --> 00:31:42,240
 environment? We're just spending time with Christians. I call this the Christian bubble.

274
00:31:42,240 --> 00:31:47,680
 We go to church, we go to Bible study, we go to something else Christian, everything Christian.

275
00:31:47,680 --> 00:31:52,880
 And so we're people who think like us, who agree with us, and that there's no challenge

276
00:31:53,680 --> 00:32:01,280
 to our faith. But guess what? You're also not shining light in the darkness. You're not living

277
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:07,280
 out the great commission that Jesus has entrusted with of making disciples of all nations.

278
00:32:07,280 --> 00:32:13,040
 You're not participating in the mission of bringing hope and healing to a broken and

279
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:19,440
 desperate world. And so while we do need Christian community, we're not meant to live exclusively in

280
00:32:19,440 --> 00:32:23,920
 it. You know, we're meant to be out and about in the streets, in the city, in our neighborhoods,

281
00:32:23,920 --> 00:32:32,480
 in our families, wherever God leads you. But then there's another reason, and that's because we're

282
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:37,680
 too assimilated to the world. You know, instead of reflecting the values of Jesus, actually our life

283
00:32:37,680 --> 00:32:46,640
 speaks world. When you look at it, over New Year's, there was the South China Morning Post

284
00:32:46,640 --> 00:32:50,400
 and social media, there was a lot of posts about a fight between two teenage girls.

285
00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:55,840
 And people were, you know, watching it, they were filming it,

286
00:32:55,840 --> 00:33:02,560
 they were pointing at them, they were laughing. But nobody stepped in, at least not for a very

287
00:33:02,560 --> 00:33:10,320
 long time. And so why is that? I think one, because people are aligned with the values

288
00:33:10,320 --> 00:33:16,640
 of the world. You think it's funny, something that actually should break our heart. You know, sometimes

289
00:33:16,640 --> 00:33:19,920
 we've become this way, where we think something's funny, that really, if you're a Jesus follower,

290
00:33:19,920 --> 00:33:30,720
 you shouldn't think it's funny. And then the second aspect is that it is easier to hide in the crowd

291
00:33:30,720 --> 00:33:36,400
 than to stick out and to do what's actually hard, and to go against the status quo,

292
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:44,080
 to try to make peace, to try to protect someone, to try to

293
00:33:44,080 --> 00:33:50,480
 follow Jesus. And so we hide in the crowd.

294
00:33:50,480 --> 00:33:54,880
 So I want to invite the worship team to come up.

295
00:33:54,880 --> 00:34:01,680
 And there was an invitation, you know, as I was preparing, there actually was a lot of wrestling

296
00:34:01,680 --> 00:34:08,880
 with how do you, you know, how should I talk about this? And what I sense God wanted to challenge us

297
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:15,920
 with is this, what I have here is, Jesus is calling you today out of your personal comfort.

298
00:34:15,920 --> 00:34:19,600
 You know, whether that's the comfort of being with a bunch of Christians all the time,

299
00:34:19,600 --> 00:34:25,040
 or whether that's like hiding in the crowd and being assimilated to the world and just

300
00:34:25,040 --> 00:34:32,800
 trying to create yourself a comfortable, non-friction life. And he's inviting you

301
00:34:32,800 --> 00:34:39,520
 and inviting us as a community into a greater faithfulness of doing the works of Jesus,

302
00:34:39,520 --> 00:34:46,240
 of shining light into darkness, of bringing hope and bringing healing and bringing salvation

303
00:34:46,240 --> 00:34:54,160
 to world, to people, to lives that desperately need it. Yes, there's going to be pushback,

304
00:34:54,160 --> 00:35:02,960
 but so what? Jesus is with us, you know, and he wants to change lives.

305
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:09,760
 He wants to advance the kingdom through his people, through his church. And I was like,

306
00:35:09,760 --> 00:35:16,720
 I was dreaming, what if this year, you know, all of us take a step forward in the faithfulness to

307
00:35:16,720 --> 00:35:24,160
 Jesus, that we decide to let go of, you know, these areas where we've chosen comfort over following Jesus?

308
00:35:24,160 --> 00:35:31,120
 What is God going to do when his church stands up and doesn't just seek to live comfortable

309
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:40,880
 lives where there's no friction and no tension with the world? Now, us actually doing that is

310
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:45,120
 always the work of the Spirit, of the Holy Spirit. We cannot conjure up our own strength,

311
00:35:46,560 --> 00:35:48,960
 but we can come to Jesus and we can tell him, "Jesus,

312
00:35:48,960 --> 00:35:52,720
 you know, I know I haven't been as faithful as I want to be.

313
00:35:52,720 --> 00:36:00,960
 Forgive me, and will you give me the grace and strength and by your Spirit, by your power to live

314
00:36:00,960 --> 00:36:08,400
 faithfully? Show me how to do it. Help me to not be discouraged when I fail so I can keep going."

315
00:36:08,400 --> 00:36:13,200
 So what I want to do right now is I just actually want to give you a little space

316
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:19,920
 just for you to talk with Jesus. And I, you know, I don't know where you are on this journey. Maybe

317
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:24,400
 you're suffering from persecution, you know, it's always possible, then talk to Jesus about that.

318
00:36:24,400 --> 00:36:30,320
 So I'm going to give a minute space, you know, for you just to commune and talk to him in prayer,

319
00:36:30,320 --> 00:36:36,800
 and then I'll pray for us and also pray for the persecuted church. All right, let's do this church.

320
00:36:36,800 --> 00:36:45,440
 Let's take some time to pray. Jesus, I thank you so much that, you know, you didn't just

321
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:52,400
 call us to live this righteous life, this faithful life, this life of love, of self-giving love, but

322
00:36:52,400 --> 00:36:57,840
 you showed us how to do it. You lived it,

323
00:36:57,840 --> 00:37:06,080
 and you suffered, but you did it. Nonetheless, rejoice him because you know what it was for.

324
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:12,960
 And Jesus, you know, each and one of our lives where we have chosen comfort over faithfully

325
00:37:12,960 --> 00:37:18,320
 following you, and maybe we hadn't even thought about it, Lord. Maybe today this just kind of

326
00:37:18,320 --> 00:37:23,440
 came up like, "Oh yeah, I kind of do that." And so, Lord, we just surrender that to you.

327
00:37:23,440 --> 00:37:33,760
 Say, "Jesus, we're sorry, and will you forgive us, and will you fill us now with your Holy Spirit,

328
00:37:34,960 --> 00:37:42,640
 and will you help us to live lives that honor you, where your love, your blessing flows through us

329
00:37:42,640 --> 00:37:51,600
 into a dark and a hurting world, where your light shines so that people, you know, come to know your

330
00:37:51,600 --> 00:37:57,520
 love, come to know you, that your kingdom is advanced." Lord, we never do that over one

331
00:37:57,520 --> 00:38:02,240
 strength. It's always by your grace. It's always by your power. It's the church and the power of

332
00:38:02,240 --> 00:38:10,720
 the Holy Spirit. And so, we pray, "Holy Spirit, come when you move in power among us," because

333
00:38:10,720 --> 00:38:14,080
 it's always your work. And we say, "We need you." We can't do this out of our own strength.

334
00:38:14,080 --> 00:38:29,520
 We're here. We're ready, Lord. Thank you, Jesus. And Jesus, we also lift up our brothers and

335
00:38:29,520 --> 00:38:36,960
 sisters around the world here in Asia and all other continents that are suffering because they

336
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:42,880
 are identifying with you, because they belong to you, that are being imprisoned, that are being

337
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:48,720
 beaten, that are being discriminated against. And Jesus, will you strengthen your people right now?

338
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:56,240
 Will you pour your Spirit over them and encourage them and give them that supernatural joy

339
00:38:57,840 --> 00:39:03,520
 that you give where they can rejoice and be glad because they belong to you, because they know you.

340
00:39:03,520 --> 00:39:09,280
 But Lord, we also pray for deliverance. We pray that you deliver our brothers and sisters from

341
00:39:09,280 --> 00:39:15,760
 persecution, that you release them from these circumstances, that you bring justice to injustice.

342
00:39:15,760 --> 00:39:22,160
 And Lord, and so we put our hope, we put our faith in you, and we pray all this in your

343
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:28,800
 precious name, Jesus. And the church says, "Amen." Church, let's worship.

